<item>
            <title>[CXF-3964] Codegen plugin tries to use classes dir as wsdl</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3964</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Under circumstances explained in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MSITE-622&quot; title=&quot;Site:site build fails with no error message&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MSITE-622&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MSITE-622&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the maven-artifact-resolver comes up with a bogus answer to resolving the WSDL artifact, and returns a classes directory!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At least, detect this and don&apos;t try to use it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Better, stop using that artifact-resolver component and call what it calls if that gets less ridiculous behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12534274">CXF-3964</key>
            <summary>Codegen plugin tries to use classes dir as wsdl</summary>
